From: Michal Luczaj <mhal@rbox.co>
Date: Mon, 9 Jun 2025 19:08:03 +0200
Subject: net: Fix TOCTOU issue in sk_is_readable()
Git-commit: 2660a544fdc0940bba15f70508a46cf9a6491230
Patch-mainline: v6.16-rc2
References: CVE-2025-38112 bsc#1245668

sk->sk_prot->sock_is_readable is a valid function pointer when sk resides
in a sockmap. After the last sk_psock_put() (which usually happens when
socket is removed from sockmap), sk->sk_prot gets restored and
sk->sk_prot->sock_is_readable becomes NULL.

This makes sk_is_readable() racy, if the value of sk->sk_prot is reloaded
after the initial check. Which in turn may lead to a null pointer
dereference.

Ensure the function pointer does not turn NULL after the check.

Fixes: 8934ce2fd081 ("bpf: sockmap redirect ingress support")
Suggested-by: Jakub Sitnicki <jakub@cloudflare.com>
Signed-off-by: Michal Luczaj <mhal@rbox.co>
Reviewed-by: Willem de Bruijn <willemb@google.com>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20250609-skisreadable-toctou-v1-1-d0dfb2d62c37@rbox.co
Signed-off-by: Jakub Kicinski <kuba@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Pedro Falcato <pfalcato@suse.de>
[pfalcato: Rewrite the patch for the corresponding bit in SLE12-SP5, tcp_stream_is_readable]
---
 net/ipv4/tcp.c |    5 +++--
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/net/ipv4/tcp.c
+++ b/net/ipv4/tcp.c
@@ -458,9 +458,10 @@ static void tcp_tx_timestamp(struct sock
 static inline bool tcp_stream_is_readable(const struct tcp_sock *tp,
 					  int target, struct sock *sk)
 {
+	struct proto *prot = READ_ONCE(sk->sk_prot);
 	return (tp->rcv_nxt - tp->copied_seq >= target) ||
-		(sk->sk_prot->stream_memory_read ?
-		sk->sk_prot->stream_memory_read(sk) : false);
+		(prot->stream_memory_read ?
+		prot->stream_memory_read(sk) : false);
 }
 
